<!-- Hero -->
<section class="section-hero section-hero--dark">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="section-hero__headline">AHG Does Not React to Policy.<br>AHG Drives It.</h1>
    <p class="section-hero__sub">Six fights. Every young person between 14 and 26.</p>
    <a href="#agenda" class="btn btn-outline btn-outline--light">SEE THE AGENDA</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Three Pillars -->
<section class="section-pillars" id="agenda">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-pillars__label">THE THREE PILLARS</span>
    <h2 class="section-pillars__headline">What We Fight For</h2>
    <div class="card-grid card-grid--three">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card__number">01</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Education Beyond the Classroom</h3>
        <p class="card__text">The system was built for compliance, not comprehension. We are rewriting what education means for the students it leaves behind.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card__number">02</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Policy That Protects the Future</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Foster care, mental health, housing, juvenile justice — every system touching young lives needs people in the room who refuse to leave.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card__number">03</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Representation</h3>
        <p class="card__text">If no one at the table has lived it, the table is incomplete. We put the people closest to the problem closest to the power.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Six Policy Issues -->
<section class="section-policy-issues" id="issues">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-policy-issues__label">THE SIX FIGHTS</span>
    <h2 class="section-policy-issues__headline">Our Policy Agenda</h2>

    <div class="policy-accordion">

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">01</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Mental Health Infrastructure in Schools</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>Every school should have a licensed counselor available every day, not once a week, not shared across buildings.</strong></p>
            <p>Young people are in crisis. The infrastructure to catch them does not exist at scale. AHG advocates for mandatory counselor-to-student ratios, trauma-informed training for all school staff, and state-level funding that treats adolescent mental health as non-negotiable.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">02</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Education System Redesign</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>The curriculum was designed for a world that no longer exists. It is time to build one that prepares students for the world they actually inherit.</strong></p>
            <p>AHG pushes for financial literacy requirements, civics education that goes beyond textbooks, career pathway integration starting in middle school, and student voices in curriculum review processes at the district and state level.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item" id="foster-care">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">03</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Foster Care Transition Reform</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>No one should age out of a system with nothing. The state that raised them owes them a real transition.</strong></p>
            <div class="policy-accordion__stats">
              <div class="policy-accordion__stat">
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-number">38,000+</span>
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-label">children in Texas foster care</span>
              </div>
              <div class="policy-accordion__stat">
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-number">1.5%</span>
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-label">earn a college degree by 24</span>
              </div>
              <div class="policy-accordion__stat">
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-number">46%</span>
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-label">experience homelessness before 26</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>AHG fights for extended foster care benefits to age 25, guaranteed housing placement for aging-out youth, mentorship mandates, and state-funded transition coordinators who stay with young people through the process.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">04</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Juvenile Justice Reform</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>A child who enters the justice system should leave it better than they entered. Right now, the opposite is true.</strong></p>
            <p>AHG demands diversion-first models, an end to juvenile solitary confinement, automatic record expungement at 18 for non-violent offenses, and restorative justice programs as a default in every jurisdiction.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">05</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Youth Representation in Civic Institutions</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>Decisions about young people are made every day in rooms without a single young person in them. That ends.</strong></p>
            <p>AHG advocates for youth advisory boards with binding authority at the city and county level, lowering the age for appointed commission seats, and paid civic fellowship programs that place 18-to-26-year-olds in government offices with real influence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">06</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Housing Access for Young Adults</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>You cannot build a life without a stable place to live. Housing is infrastructure, not a privilege.</strong></p>
            <p>AHG pushes for guaranteed transitional housing for aging-out foster youth, co-signer alternative programs, rental assistance tied to education enrollment or employment, and zoning reform that creates affordable inventory for young adults in urban centers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Advocacy -->
<section class="section-advocacy" id="advocacy">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-advocacy__inner">
      <span class="section-advocacy__label">ADVOCACY</span>
      <h2 class="section-advocacy__headline">Policy Without Pressure Is a Suggestion.</h2>
      <p class="section-advocacy__text">AHG shows up — at hearings, at councils, at statehouses. We draft language, build coalitions, and hold officials accountable by name. This is not performative. This is the work.</p>
      <a href="/get-involved" class="btn btn-primary">JOIN THE FIGHT</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.policy-accordion__trigger').forEach(function(trigger) {
    trigger.addEventListener('click', function() {
      var expanded = this.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
      var panel = this.nextElementSibling;
      var icon = this.querySelector('.policy-accordion__icon');

      this.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!expanded));
      panel.hidden = expanded;
      icon.textContent = expanded ? '+' : '–';
    });
  });
</script>
